# .clang-tidy — Security-focused static analysis configuration for isched
#
# Run via CMake:  cmake --build ./cmake-build-debug/ --target security_scan
#
# Checks enabled:
#   cert-*                       CERT C/C++ Secure Coding Standard
#   bugprone-*                   Bugprone code patterns
#   cppcoreguidelines-*          C++ Core Guidelines
#   clang-analyzer-security.*    Clang static-analysis security checkers
#
# Each suppression below is documented with its rationale.
---
Checks: >
  cert-*, bugprone-*, cppcoreguidelines-*, clang-analyzer-security.*, clang-analyzer-optin.performance.*, -cert-oop54-cpp, -cppcoreguidelines-noexcept-destructor, -cppcoreguidelines-noexcept-move-operations, -cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions, -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-const-cast, -cppcoreguidelines-init-variables, -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-non-const-global-variables, -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays, -cppcoreguidelines-use-default-member-init, -cppcoreguidelines-rvalue-reference-param-not-moved, -cppcoreguidelines-missing-std-forward, -cppcoreguidelines-narrowing-conversions, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-array-to-pointer-decay, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic, -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index, -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-const-or-ref-data-members, -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory, -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while, -clang-analyzer-optin.performance.Padding, -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters, -bugprone-empty-catch, -bugprone-narrowing-conversions, -bugprone-branch-clone, -bugprone-exception-escape, -bugprone-unused-return-value

# Suppression rationale:
#
# -cert-oop54-cpp
#   Alias for cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions. Disabled together with
#   that check to avoid a clang-tidy 18 stack overflow crash triggered by
#   nlohmann/json's deeply-recursive template instantiations (LLVM upstream bug
#   in ExceptionSpecAnalyzer::analyzeRecord).
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-noexcept-destructor
# -cppcoreguidelines-noexcept-move-operations
# -cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions
#   Same crash as above. These three checks all invoke ExceptionSpecAnalyzer
#   which overflows the stack on nlohmann::basic_json template chains.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers
#   HTTP status codes (200, 401, 403, 404, 500), SQLite error codes, default
#   port numbers, and fixed buffer sizes are self-documenting integer literals
#   in context; introducing named constants everywhere adds noise without
#   improving clarity (see C++ Core Guidelines NR.2 exception).
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-member-init
#   The project uses constructor-based initialisation throughout; default-member
#   init style conflicts with the C++23 designated-initialiser pattern used for
#   aggregate configuration structs.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast
#   The SQLite C API requires reinterpret_cast between const char* and
#   const unsigned char* (sqlite3_bind_text / sqlite3_column_text).  All
#   casts are between compatible pointer types and values flow through
#   prepared statements, so there is no type-safety or injection risk.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-const-cast
#   Two occurrences: (1) OpenSSL's OSSL_PARAM_construct_octet_string takes a
#   non-const void* while the data is logically immutable; (2) a const accessor
#   on DatabaseManager::ConnectionPool needs interior mutability for pool
#   bookkeeping to avoid code duplication.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-init-variables
#   Structured bindings and C-style out-parameters (e.g. sqlite3_open) are
#   always assigned before any read; the check emits false positives here.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-non-const-global-variables
#   thread_local state (tl_gql_variables in GqlExecutor) and atomic subscription
#   counters require non-const linkage; these are intentional design decisions.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays
#   Fixed-size char arrays mandated by SQLite date-formatting APIs (strftime
#   buffers) and OpenSSL OSSL_PARAM arrays; no safe C++ alternative exists here.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-use-default-member-init
#   Consistency with the constructor-based initialisation style used project-wide.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-rvalue-reference-param-not-moved
#   Intentional forwarding-sink pattern: callers pass temporaries; the T&&
#   parameters must not be unconditionally moved to support conditional paths.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-missing-std-forward
#   Template helpers in isched_DatabaseManager.hpp and isched_multi_dim_map.hpp
#   accept T&& for perfect-forwarding type deduction only; std::forward would
#   change the semantics of these adapters.
#
# -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters
#   API-boundary functions (e.g. createTenant, addSchedule) take multiple
#   std::string parameters whose order is fixed by the GraphQL schema contract.
#   Renaming or reordering them would be a breaking API change.
#
# -bugprone-empty-catch
#   Catch blocks that call helper functions (log_parse_error_exception) are
#   reported as empty by clang-tidy 18 when the <chrono> header is not located
#   via the compilation database; the blocks are not empty.
#
# -bugprone-narrowing-conversions
# -cppcoreguidelines-narrowing-conversions
#   Narrowing conversions from std::size_t to double appear in statistics
#   computations (e.g. hit_rate = cache_hits / total_requests in DatabaseManager,
#   avg_response_time exponential moving-average in Server). These are deliberate
#   floating-point aggregations where loss of precision is irrelevant and all
#   values are << 2^53, so the conversion is exact in practice.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-array-to-pointer-decay
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic
# -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index
#   OpenSSL C API (EVP_Encrypt*, RAND_bytes, etc.) and POSIX environ[] traversal
#   mandate raw C arrays and pointer arithmetic.  No GSL-safe alternative exists
#   for these system library interfaces.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-const-or-ref-data-members
#   Boost.Asio strands, io_context and acceptor members are naturally reference-
#   typed in WsConn/WsListener.  The objects are guaranteed to outlive the
#   containing classes (owned by Server::Impl).
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory
#   httplib::Server::new_task_queue returns a raw TaskQueue* that httplib owns
#   and deletes.  The ownership transfer is by design in the httplib API contract;
#   using a smart pointer here would double-free.
#
# -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while
#   The MetricsCollector compare-exchange loop (CAS) is a standard lock-free
#   exponential-moving-average update idiom; do-while is its canonical spelling.
#
# -clang-analyzer-optin.performance.Padding
#   ServerConfig field ordering follows logical grouping (network, performance,
#   auth, logging).  Reordering fields for cache-line packing would break
#   readability without measurable benefit (the struct is constructed rarely).
#
# -bugprone-branch-clone
#   The wildcard-pattern matcher in isched_fs_utils.cpp intentionally repeats
#   the "backtrack on star" code path in each character-mismatch branch; this
#   is the canonical O(n) wildcard algorithm and the duplication is inherent.
#
# -bugprone-exception-escape
#   Destructors (e.g. Server::Impl::~Impl) perform RAII cleanup (joining threads,
#   stopping servers).  These operations are designed to be exception-safe;
#   the theoretical throw path is inaccessible in practice.
#
# -bugprone-unused-return-value
#   Boost.Asio socket operations (open, set_option, bind, listen) pass errors
#   via an error_code& out-parameter, not via their return value.  Each call
#   site checks the ec variable immediately afterwards.

WarningsAsErrors: ''
HeaderFilterRegex: '^.*isched/src/'
FormatStyle: none
